message.content: <OUTPUT_TEXT>To keep and monitor legal volumes to ensure that the law library is up-to-date, you should regularly check for new editions or updates of legal texts, subscribe to legal publishers' update services, and maintain an organized cataloging system. Additionally, you should periodically review the library's collection to identify outdated materials and replace them with current versions. Implementing a digital tracking system can also help in monitoring the status of the library's resources efficiently.</OUTPUT_TEXT>
